The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | CCI chief case
                                                                                                               CCI chief case
                            
	Mumbai, May 9 (PTI): The family of Kamaljeet Rajpal, the Cricket Club of India chief, said he shot himself in the head accidentally yesterday while cleaning his gun.         
	Rajpal, who is facing allegations of sending a woman CCI member a sexually explicit video clip, has been admitted to Bombay Hospital and has undergone surgery. Sources said he was out of danger.        
	Rajpals wife Rita and son Suveer have said in their statements that he was cleaning the gun when it went off, an officer of Cuffe Parade police station said.        
	Rita, Suveer, Rajpals daughter and some of her friends were at their home in Cuffe Parade when they heard a single shot and rushed to Rajpals bedroom.        
	We have recorded the statements of family members but they are all saying the shooting was accidental, the officer said. His family members said he may have been tense after attending court proceedings yesterday but he had not mentioned anything to them.         
	A sessions court hearing Rajpals anticipatory bail application has adjourned the matter till Monday.         
	The police also said they had found no suicide note written by Rajpal to indicate he wanted to end his life.                                                                                                                                                                           
